This paper deals with image aesthetic quality assessment, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses high-level features based on human perception and principles of group photography, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The authors also mention the use of machine learning algorithms for aesthetic assessment, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
